 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.2","title":"epic(opentui-import): Source ingestion and static-dynamic understanding","description":"## Background
Ingest OpenTUI repositories safely and extract high-fidelity static/dynamic semantics needed for deterministic downstream translation.

## Scope
- Intake runner for local/git sources with locked snapshots.
- Toolchain/context resolution (JS/TS config, module graph, entrypoints).
- Semantic extraction for UI composition, state/effects, style tokens, and capability assumptions.
- Sandbox hardening, secret redaction, and adversarial ingestion checks.
- Unit + E2E ingestion verification with replayable structured logs.

## Success Criteria
1. Ingestion yields deterministic semantic artifacts for identical source snapshots.
2. Untrusted source analysis enforces sandbox/resource/security policies with auditable logs.
3. Redaction pipeline prevents secret leakage while preserving diagnostic usefulness.
4. E2E adversarial ingestion fixtures pass with reproducible replay commands.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:28:19.275347982Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-24T22:22:54.942934929Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["analysis","ingestion","opentui-import"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:28:19.275347982Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.2.1","title":"task(opentui-import ingestion): Implement project intake runner (local path, git URL, locked snapshot)","description":"Objective: Build intake runner that accepts local project paths or git URLs, materializes reproducible snapshots, and records source fingerprints for deterministic migration.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n1. Intake supports pinned commit checkout and immutable working snapshot.\n2. Snapshot metadata includes source hash, lockfiles, and toolchain versions.\n3. Intake errors are classified (auth, network, missing files, incompatible repo).","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:29:22.344039782Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-25T02:12:10.724114855Z","closed_at":"2026-02-25T02:12:10.724095819Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ingestion","intake","opentui-import"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:29:22.344039782Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.2.10","title":"task(opentui-import ingestion tests): E2E ingestion script with deterministic replay logging","description":"Objective: Implement an end-to-end ingestion script that runs full source analysis on curated fixtures and emits deterministic JSONL traces suitable for replay triage.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n1. Script runs all ingestion stages and validates manifest completeness.\n2. Re-running with same seed/context yields byte-identical traces.\n3. Failures include stage-specific diagnostics and reproduction commands.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:29:38.743395709Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-24T22:20:11.766528062Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["e2e","ingestion","opentui-import","test"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.10","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T22:20:11.766461256Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.10","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:29:38.743395709Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.10","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:37:14.566609232Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
